---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { Container } from "@/components/layout/Container";
---

<Layout
    title="Steps to Opening a Daycare | Childcare Business Plan"
    description="Your path to opening a daycare depends on your state's licensing process and local requirements. Understand what affects your timeline and approach."
>
    <!-- HERO SECTION -->
    <section class="py-12 md:py-20">
        <Container size="md">
            <div class="text-center mb-8 md:mb-12">
                <span
                    class="inline-block px-3 py-1 rounded-full bg-teal-100 text-teal-700 text-xs font-semibold mb-3"
                >
                    The Journey
                </span>
                <h1
                    class="text-2xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 md:mb-6"
                >
                    YOUR Path to Opening
                </h1>
                <p class="text-base md:text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
                    Opening a daycare involves navigating state licensing, local
                    regulations, and market preparation. The complexity and
                    timeline of your journey depends entirely on where you're
                    opening.
                </p>
            </div>
        </Container>
    </section>

    <!-- FACTORS SECTION -->
    <section class="py-8 md:py-16">
        <Container size="md">
            <div
                class="glass-panel rounded-2xl md:rounded-3xl p-6 md:p-10 mb-6 md:mb-8"
            >
                <h2
                    class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 md:mb-6"
                >
                    What Affects Your Timeline
                </h2>
                <div
                    class="space-y-4 text-sm md:text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed"
                >
                    <p>
                        Some states have streamlined licensing processes that
                        take weeks, while others involve months of paperwork,
                        inspections, and waiting periods. The type of facility
                        you're opening—home-based versus center-based—triggers
                        completely different regulatory pathways.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Your existing situation matters too. Do you already have
                        a suitable space or need to find one? Are you converting
                        a home or building out a commercial property? Each of
                        these factors changes which obstacles you'll face.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Local requirements layer on top of state regulations.
                        Fire marshal inspections, health department approvals,
                        zoning clearances, and business registrations all have
                        their own timelines and prerequisites.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </Container>
    </section>

    <!-- WHY GENERIC FAILS SECTION -->
    <section class="py-8 md:py-16">
        <Container size="md">
            <div class="glass-panel rounded-2xl md:rounded-3xl p-6 md:p-10">
                <h2
                    class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 md:mb-6"
                >
                    Why Online Advice Often Conflicts
                </h2>
                <div
                    class="space-y-4 text-sm md:text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed"
                >
                    <p>
                        Generic timelines and step-by-step guides fall apart
                        when they hit your specific reality. An article that
                        says "getting licensed takes 3 months" might be right
                        for one state and completely wrong for yours.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        The order of operations matters enormously, and it's
                        determined by your state's licensing agency, your local
                        jurisdiction, and your business model. Following the
                        wrong sequence means redoing work or missing deadlines.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        What you need isn't more generic advice—you need a
                        roadmap built on your state's specific requirements,
                        your facility type, and your current starting point.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </Container>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA SECTION -->
    <section class="py-12 md:py-20">
        <Container size="md">
            <div
                class="glass-panel rounded-2xl md:rounded-3xl p-6 md:p-10 text-center border-2 border-teal-200/50 bg-gradient-to-br from-teal-50/50 to-white/50"
            >
                <h2
                    class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3 md:mb-4"
                >
                    See How Much YOU Could Make in Your State
                </h2>
                <p class="text-sm md:text-base text-gray-600 mb-4 md:mb-6">
                    Before planning your path, understand your income potential
                    based on your state's regulations.
                </p>
                <a
                    href="/#calculator"
                    class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-teal-600 hover:bg-teal-700 text-white font-medium px-6 py-3 md:px-8 md:py-4 shadow-lg transition-all text-sm md:text-base"
                >
                    Use the Free Calculator →
                </a>
            </div>
        </Container>
    </section>
</Layout>
